        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer81606980" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8013791253447570383">My favourite Munro. I love it and am a bit ambivalent at the same time. The stories are so close to real life, so undisguised, and about such difficult subjects, that reading them is a bit like going to the therapist. It&apos;s a really intense experience. She reaches somewhere in my psyche and exposes truths and issues I am unwilling to explore on my own. She shows scenarios that may happen, and if they happened, they would be painful. To use an analogy: reading Munro for me is a bit like passing by</span>
  <span id="freeText8013791253447570383" style="display:none">My favourite Munro. I love it and am a bit ambivalent at the same time. The stories are so close to real life, so undisguised, and about such difficult subjects, that reading them is a bit like going to the therapist. It's a really intense experience. She reaches somewhere in my psyche and exposes truths and issues I am unwilling to explore on my own. She shows scenarios that may happen, and if they happened, they would be painful. To use an analogy: reading Munro for me is a bit like passing by an accident and having that irresistible urge to slow down and look, no matter how gory it is. <br />She is excellent, though, and an absolute master of structure, intrigue and style here, and this collection of short stories is the best thing I have read by her so far.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8013791253447570383" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

