        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1648858687" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15446122431452628811">At some point in my life, I stopped liking short stories. Reading them, no matter how well crafted, raised feelings of impatience in me. In respect to the authors of this genre, I decided to avoid it for years. But... Alice Munro was breathed at me as the quintessential short story writer, in 2003, by a few avid readers I didn&apos;t know well and I decided that it was time to break my fast and immerse myself respectfully in Munro&apos;s art. <br/><br/>Conclusion: Munro does write beautifully. I, however, continue </span>
  <span id="freeText15446122431452628811" style="display:none">At some point in my life, I stopped liking short stories. Reading them, no matter how well crafted, raised feelings of impatience in me. In respect to the authors of this genre, I decided to avoid it for years. But... Alice Munro was breathed at me as the quintessential short story writer, in 2003, by a few avid readers I didn't know well and I decided that it was time to break my fast and immerse myself respectfully in Munro's art. <br /><br />Conclusion: Munro does write beautifully. I, however, continue to not be fond of short stories no matter how well-crafted. A vignette is not enough story for me; I want and need more. My loss, I know, but they still irritate me. Ah, well...</span>
  <a data-text-id="15446122431452628811" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
